    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-04-05T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-04-05T15:00:00-05:00" n="928"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d928">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">561.35E1/276: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-05T20:00:00+00:00"
                            >April 5, 1937—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 5—5:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. The Conference was opened by MacDonald<note n="10" xml:id="d928fn10">J. Ramsay
                        MacDonald, British Lord President of the Council.</note> as President at 11
                    a.m. today. Ormsby-Gore<note n="11" xml:id="d928fn11">W. G. A. Ormsby-Gore,
                        British Secretary of State for the Colonies.</note> was elected Vice
                    President and will preside at future meetings. A steering committee<note n="12"
                        xml:id="d928fn12">Otherwise referred to as the “Bureau”.</note> was
                    appointed consisting of the President and the Vice President of the Conference
                    and the chief delegates from France, Germany, Poland, Cuba, the <pb facs="0948"
                        n="936" xml:id="pg_936"/> United States, Czechoslovakia, Australia,
                    Netherlands, and the President of the International Sugar Committee. It was
                    agreed that future meetings should be closed to the press and all publicity
                    should be handled by the Press Bureau of the Secretariat.</p>
                <p>At the first meeting of the steering committee this afternoon a statistical
                    committee of seven experts including Hutson was appointed. At the plenary
                    session this afternoon, which was closed to the press, Buencamino and I made
                    statements as modified by the Department.<note n="13" xml:id="d928fn13">See <hi
                            rend="italic">Proceedings and Documents of the Conference</hi>, pp. 29
                        and 33.</note> Five other delegations made general statements of
                    position.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
